# hilavitkutin-extensions-macros

Proc-macro companion to `hilavitkutin-extensions`. Ships the primary
`#[export_extension]` attribute that emits the `#[repr(C)]` descriptor
constant, the well-known exported symbol fn, the capability table, and
per-capability C-ABI trampolines from a user-authored extension struct
that implements the capability traits.

Necessarily `std`-backed at macro execution time (proc-macros run in
the compiler host context). Emitted output is `no_std`-compatible and
compiles under the same restrictions as the rest of the hilavitkutin
stack. Intended to be wrapped by downstream consumer contract crates
under domain-named macros (for example `#[viola::plugin]`) that expand
to `#[export_extension]` internally.
